IZqYsXBZ910LRmCGWL-ewXqkOfqW7FByyFXr46mnLc-qH_Bw7639vEL4KJHpxxOUopBzEwPaoNQ=
W98niZj9YDb3cA-20OxcxdDabpUMD-v2UleQqw6Zh_2Xv5xcOLxLnSEa9_PFny9VwygD7QfuvVj=
0pv3umPA3M2zK9RujVIj40LwmcsPzY5fTSNjUirSlW3sXeGf6F_qE7DT" rel=3D"" style=3D=
"color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">case study</a> for the value =
of high-quality photography. People and businesses alike would need, and be=
 willing to pay for, higher-quality photos.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a=
1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Then there wa=
s the <strong>market structure</strong>. I didn&#8217;t know this until Mat=
t told me, but there was only one services industry more fragmented pre-mar=
ketplaces than the photography industry: taxis. Putting a digital marketpla=
ce on top of that industry resulted in multiple multi-deca-billion dollar c=
ompanies, including Uber, Lyft, and Didi.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a=
1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Unlike those co=
mpanies, though, who would need to await the arrival of self-driving cars t=
o produce software margins, the margin expansion opportunities for photogra=
phy were manifold, from editing to storage to asset management to distribut=
ion.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26p=
x; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">You&#8217;d just need to grab the consumer market as=
 a wedge, build up liquidity, write some code, sell the whole package to en=
terprises, and Bob&#8217;s your uncle.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-=
size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Well, I got to ask Matt =
directly whether the plan all along was to go from B2C to B2B to SaaS and i=
nfrastructure.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-h=
eight: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">The answer was a resounding, Australian-ac=
cented &#8220;no.&#8221; (noyr?)&nbsp;</p><a href=3D"https://email.mg2.subs=
tack.com/c/eJxFkMtqxDAMRb8mXga_MnUWXhTKlEK_YDbBDyVjJrGDI0_I39czWRQuEkhcXXSc=
